## Class Stacking Prohibition Rules (ABSOLUTE — Anti-Hallucination)

These rules prevent the most common AI code generation errors in this codebase.

### Rule N-1 — Shortcut expansion values NEVER co-exist with the shortcut itself

**ABSOLUTE RULE**: When using a shortcut, NEVER simultaneously write the atomic classes that the shortcut expands into.

| FORBIDDEN | Why | Correct |
|-----------|-----|---------|
| `flex items-center justify-center center` | `center` already IS `flex items-center justify-center` | `center` |
| `w-full h-full layout-full` | `layout-full` already IS `w-full h-full` | `layout-full` |
| `transition-all duration-md motion-lift` | `motion-lift` already includes transition | `motion-lift` |
| `flex-1 min-h-0 flex flex-col overflow-hidden col-fill` | `col-fill` already IS this expansion | `col-fill` |

**Self-check**: Before committing any class list, verify: does any shortcut you wrote expand into classes also present in the same list? If yes, remove the redundant atomic classes.

---

### Rule N-2 — Flex atomic classes are mutually exclusive with flex shortcuts

**ABSOLUTE RULE**: Flex shortcuts already contain `flex`. NEVER prepend `flex`, `flex-row`, `flex-col`, `items-*`, or `justify-*` to a flex shortcut.

Flex shortcuts (each already contains `flex`):
`center`, `row-center`, `row-between`, `row-start`, `row-end`, `col-center`, `col-between`, `col-stretch`, `col-fill`

| FORBIDDEN | Correct |
|-----------|---------|
| `flex row-between` | `row-between` |
| `flex col-center` | `col-center` |
| `flex flex-col col-fill` | `col-fill` |
| `flex items-center row-start` | `row-start` |

---

### Rule N-3 — `.pv-input-fluid` is PrimeVue-exclusive

**ABSOLUTE RULE**: `.pv-input-fluid` is ONLY for wrapping PrimeVue input components to force `width: 100%` on `.p-inputtext`.
- FORBIDDEN: `<div class="pv-input-fluid">` — generic divs do not use this class
- For general full-width: use `w-full` (standalone, never combined with `layout-full`)

---

### Rule N-4 — Avoid stacking redundant interaction utilities

Do not duplicate motion/transition: e.g. do not add `hover:-translate-y-1` on top of `motion-lift` unless you intentionally override.

---

### Rule N-5 — Anti-Utility-Soup: Rule of 7

**[LAW]: Raw utility count MUST ≤ 7** on structural elements. If > 7 and the combination is structural, find a shortcut or split into nested wrappers.

| Raw utility soup | Prefer instead |
|------------------|----------------|
| `flex flex-col flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-hidden gap-md p-md bg-card rounded-md shadow-sm border border-border` | `col-fill` + `gap-md p-md bg-card rounded-md shadow-sm border border-border` |
| `flex items-center justify-center w-full h-full` | `center layout-full` |

**Intent**: Normal UI elements with up to 7 classes are acceptable. This rule triggers when layout macro shortcuts are being ignored.
